{
  "texts": [
    "Choice of Multilingual High-Resource Language Datasets Prior work on X-ICL with alignment (Tanwar et al., 2023) conduct their study on Multilingual Amazon Review Corpus (MARC) (Keung et al., 2020), Cross-language Sentiment (CLS) (Prettenhofer and Stein, 2010), and HatEval (Basile et al., 2019).",
    "We considered using these datasets as our high-resource languages dataset.",
    "Nonetheless, we found that both MARC and CLS datasets are no longer available 4, leaving us with only HatEval dataset.",
    "Since HatEval only covers English and Spanish, we do not incorporate it in our study.",
    "Instead, we incorporate the TweetSentimentMultilingual dataset (Barbieri et al., 2022) which covers 7 relatively high-resource languages in our study."
  ]
}